# AI Trading Arena — UI Design System

When building or modifying anything in `apps/web`, follow this system. Do not introduce one-off styles.

## Aesthetic

- **Professional + memetic**: clean financial dashboard meets dev/hacker culture
- **Light mode**: off-white bg (`--bg: #f7f7f5`), white cards, thin gray borders
- **Typography**: Instrument Serif for titles/logo, DM Sans for body, JetBrains Mono for data/prices/chat
- **Reference**: Alpha Arena by Nof1 — ticker bar, model tabs, ModelChat feed, update banners

## Layout shell

Every page uses `Shell` from `components/layout/Shell.tsx`:
- `Header` — logo, nav (Live / Leaderboard / Models / Portfolio), CTA
- `TabTickerBar` — aggregate + per-model tabs, scrolling asset ticker (BTC ETH SOL BNB XRP)
- `shell-main` content area

Nav keys: `live` | `leaderboard` | `models` | `portfolio`

## Reuse before creating

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Page wrapper | `Shell` |
| Cards | `.card`, `.card-header`, `.card-body` |
| Tables | `LeaderboardTable` or `.data-table` |
| Model grid | `ModelCard` |
| Live feed | `ModelChat` |
| Staking | `StakePanel` |
| User account | `PortfolioPanel` + `useUser()` |
| Formatting | `lib/format.ts` |
| Model colors/tags | `lib/model-meta.ts` |
| Ticker prices | `lib/market-prices.ts` |
| API calls | `lib/api.ts` |

## Copy tone

- Concise, slightly memetic ("monk mode", "paper money", "vibes")
- Data stays precise — monospace, formatted USD, signed percentages
- No lorem ipsum; use domain language (cycles, stakes, LONG/SHORT/FLAT)

## Colors & badges

- PnL positive: `--green`, negative: `--red`
- Side badges: `.badge-long`, `.badge-short`, `.badge-flat`
- Provider badges: `.badge-provider-{mock|anthropic|openai|google}`
- Model tab tints: `.tab-green`, `.tab-yellow`, `.tab-pink`, `.tab-blue`, `.tab-purple`

## New pages checklist

1. Wrap in `Shell` with correct `activeNav`
2. Use `.page-title` + `.page-subtitle`
3. Handle API offline with `.error-banner`
4. Client interactivity → `"use client"` + existing hooks
5. Add styles to `globals.css` tokens only — no inline style sprawl unless dynamic

## Do not

- Switch to dark mode or new color palettes
- Add CSS-in-JS libraries or Tailwind (not in project)
- Build pages without the shared shell/ticker
- Hardcode prices — use `quotesForCycle(cycle)` from latest cycle
